						               													<description>There are persons who like numbers, for whom the letters represent a &amp;quot;Karma&amp;quot; in his lives. On the opposite side there are persons who prefer the words and the numbers are an absolute Karma.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game there are 104 tiles with letters on one side and numbers/math symbols on the other. In the first stage of the game you should first put all the 104 tiles on the table in a random order with the letters face up, forming a 10x10 square + 4 extra tiles at the sides of rows 4 and 6 (two extra tiles per row). Then you and your opponent will shift turns for moving your tokens for picking the tiles (you pick the tiles where your token was at the start of the move). &amp;#10;After there are no more tiles to pick with legal movements then is the start of the stage 2.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the stage 2 you should form words using your picked tiles. Every player will form his own personal board with his tiles, using scrabble-like rules. The more letters used and words formed the better score you will get.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the stage 3, the players must use the same tiles but with the numbers/symbol faced up and using the same scrabble-like rules  to form equations. And again, the more tiles used and equations formed, the better score you will get.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the player with most point after adding score of both stages 2 and 3.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game can also start with the numbers/symbols faced up on the stage 1. In this case, the &amp;quot;stage 3&amp;quot; will be the second one and the &amp;quot;stage 2&amp;quot; will be the last one.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
